<br>May 4, 2013 &#150; 	Thank You so much for this wonderful site! Yay! <br>I have been searching online and can find no evidence of what's become of Patricio Lafcadio Hearn's personal, eccentric, rare and carefully selected international collection of books left first with Alden, and then to Gould.  Does anyone know? 
<br>Thank you to Edward Larocque Tinker for the fittingly, beautifully written account of Hearn's early life in "Lafcadio Hearn's American Days" (1924) and to you, Mr. Trussel.  So glad to find this lovely cache...
<p align=right><b><i>Ana Bon-Bon</i></b></p>

